---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About — igiveideas"
	description="Why igiveideas exists: the big AI labs optimise for scale, not taste. Branding needs taste, psychology and human connection."
	path="/about"
>
	<section class="page">
		<h1>About</h1>

		<p>
			<strong>igiveideas</strong> is a small workshop with one belief: the output from AI is
			<em>tasteless</em>, and taste is exactly what branding is made of.
		</p>

		<p>
			The big labs — anthropic, openai, google — are brilliant at scale. But a brand is not a
			scaling problem. It is a <em>taste</em> problem, a <em>psychology</em> problem, a
			<em>human connection</em> problem. Those don't come out of a prompt by default. You have to
			add them back in.
		</p>

		<p>
			So the question I keep asking is the one on the home page: <em>how do you run a business like
			Leonardo da Vinci?</em> Curious, patient, unafraid to leave things unfinished until they are
			right. Part artist, part engineer, all judgement.
		</p>

		<p>
			If that resonates, drop an idea into the box on the <a href="/">home page</a> and I'll send a
			little magic to your inbox.
		</p>
	</section>
</Layout>

<style>
	.page {
		max-width: 65ch;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	h1 {
		font-weight: 500;
		font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 5vw, 2.6rem);
		margin: 8px 0 18px;
	}

	p {
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		margin: 0 0 18px;
	}

	a {
		color: var(--accent);
	}
</style>
